From 9a0c2ebd89c3708e97d68b3095140fb960e1ca54 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ivan Melnikov <mail@melnoff.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 00:16:32 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(updater): GitHub Releases-based update checker

Adds Core::SovagramUpdater: on startup (30s delay), queries
api.github.com/repos/<SOVAGRAM_RELEASES_REPO>/releases/latest,
compares tag_name against the compile-time SOVAGRAM_BUILD_ID.
If different, shows a confirm box with a link to the release page
for manual download.

CMake: SOVAGRAM_BUILD_ID is auto-populated from the GITHUB_SHA env
var when building inside GitHub Actions, or can be passed manually
via -D SOVAGRAM_BUILD_ID=<sha>. SOVAGRAM_RELEASES_REPO defaults to
melnoff/tdesktop and can be overridden via -D.

If SOVAGRAM_BUILD_ID is empty (local dev), the check is skipped.
Does not touch the original desktop.telegram.org updater, which
simply never finds valid signed updates for our unofficial build.
